{"id": "ef3afa7cb440184080b7b26c107a48b5289eb883ca180953f9d897f4f1340156", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:0", "text": "A camera model that approximates a number of real world physical effects."}
{"id": "7ba41dc8df6f06d55e4eb6e53a214f0a2533a445dda0e385ab038832e93e8434", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:1", "text": "This supports all of the traditional prman perspective camera settings including shaped motion blur and bokeh."}
{"id": "15f3153f8bb70420c2921a292cbce6089c2d6acf84bcf78aa514fed1ed07851f", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:2", "text": "Some examples of the effects PxrCamera can do:"}
{"id": "8999770491ab58722c68b298217a108be14242f5bb83be68f89cb16c1dec6d37", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:3", "text": "Barrel Distortion / Chromatic Aberration / Split Diopter / Tilt-Shift / Vignetting"}
{"id": "f87c40c26317501d444a391bbe8f374b86f090193ec19f39c46ec9a4f049d8c8", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:4", "text": "Standard Parameters"}
{"id": "864fa36ee7f548aa374b40b7f4978ba52aaf4a1cb54d5a4213759d53bb3f81dd", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:17", "text": "fov"}
{"id": "d853592dcae43577874d107b816c83875ad67a0a3e57153f932dbc8fdbf921ee", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:6", "text": "Field of view (FOV) in degrees. For rectangular images this is normally the FOV along the narrower image dimension."}
{"id": "835cf0e324f32d92d3cb55e4eb02fd9a98c5162dff7e33f81a136cb50b81827e", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:7", "text": "Below is a conversion table for standard prime lenses to their horizontal fov value"}
{"id": "fce032b4f0f6e6e0bc6e93c61658ebaa5a499de4403fd4febd27253fbd4d491f", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:8", "text": "lens mm"}
{"id": "72c60c3799a6e27d9124a2c08b0248d0c07b8ab9b36cafdd825391db882a9c3b", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:9", "text": "Horizontal fov"}
{"id": "326921594e806314e3bafbea9cb0d4bcb6bb43d2743850ab15971d90216f2c8c", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:10", "text": "18mm"}
{"id": "5b91a77b055484008303f4f7e8ee5ba086ab2551c5c07c52fa2b2ec2fc3d860e", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:11", "text": "35mm"}
{"id": "88463cae8afcb03629384e832bc464e7be2117a3fc5c7f86d9402c2d2d79555f", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:12", "text": "50mm"}
{"id": "91b8eaebd47e01e8fd33efa942146d9a915e7dd651ada1bf1a397369d7ebd58c", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:13", "text": "85mm"}
{"id": "4ae982fc7a86c4a90657c927f7d3e92eb5906244c0facf4beebd15e37bec1cc5", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:14", "text": "100mm"}
{"id": "3e123e67db0c5b06c2025b9a2a008908092c9a706d51275c90b219ea37cd77a5", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:15", "text": "135mm"}
{"id": "46e463f5bd45890e0d486e866bcb0f09fca71fe43a96ac61e5facdb34d124dad", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:16", "text": "Therefore, to mimick a 50mm prime lens with the PxrCamera, you would enter the value of 39.6 in the FOV parameter"}
{"id": "fd486cedbca4bd86fe9d1dcea7105fd668d1c866eec492ce063a88024399c5f9", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:18", "text": "(end)"}
{"id": "f9bcdd8a4984b9391954601b5d1267d8e538559c501df2ec6c0b727aaa561033", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:19", "text": "Field of view (FOV) in degrees. Used to motion blur fast zooms. 0.0 means it is the same during the rendering"}
{"id": "903fc5b5e52539d14802e37da0fe7242e556519932a87808fb86a22a2f092070", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:20", "text": "F-stop"}
{"id": "ae5bcf6f9f7586da88874c566d92299df4c5db21bf0d9daee6893da671229da6", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:21", "text": "Aperture size, controls depth of field blurriness. High values emulate a pinhole camera and depth of field is disabled."}
{"id": "602c4a8f8f3d97616b60f34cf1a8f94f94f2dbf69867cfd540ce289288cdc3f8", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:22", "text": "Focal Length"}
{"id": "eb9502d143761b63cc08b72794cfb67e46c458854aacba7a4ac0681916d03bb9", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:23", "text": "The focal length of the camera in scene units measured from the camera lens. High F-stop values disable this."}
{"id": "6a4a56ccaceecd31702a15ae4ae31738ff96c8279911cb9e6d42ca9bc3c9fbf7", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:24", "text": "Focal Distance"}
{"id": "a0d418f15a15df98194e570523f801b04ac1012963b6edc5d0993e87e5536675", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:25", "text": "Distance to the focal plane where objects are in focus, measured in scene units from the camera to the object. High F-stop values disable this."}
{"id": "135435a183a44c4c711951dad7ce67cf6b5de365c3b37af3e0aef962847874a5", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:26", "text": "Aperture"}
{"id": "1f7fb3241b72830b032414ddfea47945eab1c00fe292ecef33e3d7a39f8280d0", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:27", "text": "Tilt-Shift"}
{"id": "feb9cb8c358384b9d2e9269d7420857f2207b8e432d758dfc963ebdcb5d09611", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:28", "text": "Lens Distortion"}
{"id": "3cab5b63e00a74cf4b3a86c256f10ac401d9600b605588cfc0c709f4b9e76bd8", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:29", "text": "DOF Distortion"}
{"id": "22e6deb75a542bb3a22f9f4193b556aa8eb4de9b0b7b82a438b97c242a6eaf3a", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:30", "text": "Split Diopter"}
{"id": "f6f207761ca724f892e10a15deec54c9da37498b54c75d8ecec031339f649715", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:31", "text": "Chromatic Aberration"}
{"id": "04d0d76278ebbd6585726f5073ba823a5d2e33adf90c50c2009915897fc6f48a", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:32", "text": "Vignetting"}
{"id": "c5e968362595acd5ac48947b34998234c595e1f9e4a7f852107eb5eb20ed984f", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:33", "text": "Camera Shutter"}
{"id": "a6fa4a8cd10cf3f56bf6e4d46cda70edfbfa4f83a4ace9f12aef038b8cfa5cd2", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:34", "text": "PxrCamera Advanced"}
{"id": "a91c19f549360567fcc16f614789919066a9c0883084d75d4ad376061b9dd09b", "item_id": "b5e443aea6:35", "text": "Enhance"}
